<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>9 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RT-8609 SERIES - REASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="4">
            <title>GEAR SHIFT LEVER HOUSING ASSEMBLY</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the gear shift lever housing secured in a vise, install the spade pin in the bore
                    of the housing tower (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13029b3">inset, Figure 113</hotlnk>). If previously removed, install the O-ring in
                    the tower groove.
                </para>
                <figure id="f13029b3" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13029b3" filename="../figg13/G13029B3.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 113. Install Spade Pin</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the gear shift lever in the housing with the spade pin in the lever ball slot (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13029b4">Figure 114</hotlnk>) and install the tension spring washer over the ball,
                    dished-side up (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13029b4">inset</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f13029b4" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13029b4" filename="../figg13/G13029B4.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 114. Position Gear Shift Lever in Housing and Install Tension Spring Washer
                    </caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the tension spring under the lugs in the housing,
                    <emph type="bold">seating one coil at a time</emph>
                    (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13029b5">Figure 115</hotlnk>). Use of a spring driving tool is recommended.
                </para>
                <figure id="f13029b5" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13029b5" filename="../figg13/G13029B5.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 115. Install Tension Spring Under Lugs</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the assembly from the vise and install the rubber boot over the gear shift lever
                    and against the housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13029b6">Figure 116</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f13029b6" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13029b6" filename="../figg13/G13029B6.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 116. Install Rubber Boot Over Gear Shift Lever</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
